// iosApp/Configurations/Dev.xcconfig
//
// Build settings for the iOS "Debug-Dev" variant (SHY-0104) — the sibling
// of the Android `dev` product flavor declared in `app/build.gradle.kts`.
//
// Debug-Dev runs against the PUBLIC dev backend (Firebase project
// `shytalk-dev` via the bundled GoogleService-Info.plist +
// `https://dev-api.shytalk.shyden.co.uk`) WITH the test-persona picker
// enabled, so real-iPhone dev journey/regression gauntlets run exactly as
// the Android dev flavor does — WITHOUT exposing the local emulator stack to
// the LAN (which would require the reverted `0.0.0.0` emulator rebind).
//
// Registered as the baseConfigurationReference of the project-level
// Debug-Dev XCBuildConfiguration by scripts/ios/add-dev-configuration.rb.
//
// The compile condition that selects iOSApp.swift's dev branch (DEV_BACKEND)
// is stamped onto the Debug-Dev configs by that script — NOT here — because a
// cloned config's own SWIFT_ACTIVE_COMPILATION_CONDITIONS would override an
// xcconfig value that lacks `$(inherited)`. Keeping the flag in the pbxproj
// (asserted by ios-dev-configuration.test.js) is the reliable single source.
//
// Variable contract:
//   DEV_QA_PERSONAS_PASSWORD — shared credential for the seeded dev test
//     personas. EMPTY by default so a build WITHOUT the build-time override
//     fails CLOSED: the picker hides rather than shipping a blank/placeholder
//     credential. The real value is injected at BUILD TIME, never committed —
//     scripts/ios/build-debug-dev.sh passes it as an xcodebuild command-line
//     build-setting override sourced from ~/.shytalk/dev-personas.env
//     (the PERSONAS_PASSWORD entry). Info.plist exposes the value to Swift as
//     the `DevQaPersonasPassword` key via `$(DEV_QA_PERSONAS_PASSWORD)`. The
//     Release config never defines this var, so the key resolves to empty
//     there — the credential is ABSENT from any distributable IPA (the
//     security guarantee).
//
//   KOTLIN_FRAMEWORK_BUILD_TYPE — the KMP/Compose Gradle plugin's
//     "Compile Kotlin Framework" build phase infers debug-vs-release from the
//     Xcode CONFIGURATION name, recognising only the literal `Debug`/`Release`.
//     A custom name like `Debug-Dev` defeats that heuristic ("Unable to detect
//     Kotlin framework build type"), so the type MUST be stated explicitly.
//     Debug-Dev is a debug build → `debug`. (Single-config xcconfig, so this is
//     unambiguous here — unlike the shared Local.xcconfig, which fronts both
//     Debug-Local and Release-Local and therefore can't carry one value.)
//
// xcconfig syntax: expansion is `$(VAR)` — NOT shell `${VAR}`; `//` comments.
//
// Pinned by: express-api/tests/scripts/ios-dev-xcconfig.test.js

DEV_QA_PERSONAS_PASSWORD =
KOTLIN_FRAMEWORK_BUILD_TYPE = debug
